TankPilot Phase 4B – Live Dashboard Mode

Role

You are a senior UI/UX engineer specializing in automotive interfaces.

Build a premium live dashboard inspired by modern luxury vehicles.

Do not copy Tesla’s interface directly.

Instead, create an original design inspired by Tesla, Apple Wallet, Flighty, and Rivian.

Goal

When the user starts a drive, TankPilot transforms into a distraction-safe digital dashboard.

Display

Large current speed

Digital Twin vehicle

Estimated fuel remaining

Safe driving range

Confidence

Current RPM (if available)

Coolant temperature

Battery voltage

Outside temperature (when available)

Current trip time

Distance driven

Compass heading

Design

Dark charcoal background

Minimal chrome

Massive typography

Smooth spring animations

No skeuomorphic gauges

Subtle depth

Rounded cards

Vehicle-centered layout

The digital twin is the focal point.

Dashboard Behavior

Automatically switch into Dashboard Mode when:

* Driving is detected
* Bluetooth connects to the vehicle
* Android Auto launches
* CarPlay launches

Allow manual entry as well.

Landscape mode should resemble a modern instrument cluster.

Safety

Large glanceable information.

No tiny text.

No distracting animations.

Respect accessibility and reduced-motion settings.

Dashboard updates smoothly without flicker.

Never block navigation instructions.
